## SECTION 1 — PROJECT IDENTITY

App name: GRIIT — always double-I. Never GRIT, never Grit, never grit.
Wordmark display: G R I I T (spaced, uppercase, exactly like this)
Tagline: "Discipline is not optional."
Concept: Duolingo for discipline meets Strava for self-improvement.
Audience: Males 18–30. Mental toughness, physical resilience, daily habit-building.
Platform: React Native + Expo (iOS + Android, managed workflow — never eject)
Repository: https://github.com/abdelayaseen-netizen/GRIIT.git
Backend URL: grit-backend-production.up.railway.app

### GRIIT SPELLING — ZERO TOLERANCE
Before EVERY commit, run:
```powershell
Get-ChildItem -Recurse -Filter "*.tsx" app/, src/ | Select-String "\bGRIT\b" | Select-Object -First 20
Get-ChildItem -Recurse -Filter "*.ts" lib/, backend/ | Select-String "\bGRIT\b" | Select-Object -First 20
```
Fix every single-I "GRIT" in user-facing strings before committing.
Exception only: legacy variable names that are not user-facing and predate this rule.

