## SECTION 2 — TECH STACK

### Frontend
- React Native + Expo SDK (managed workflow)
- expo-router for file-based routing
- TypeScript — no `any` types unless absolutely necessary with a comment explaining why
- Zustand for client state
- TanStack React Query for server state
- Lucide React Native for all icons
- RevenueCat for in-app purchases (scaffolded — do not remove)

### Backend
- Hono + tRPC deployed on Railway
- Backend folder: `backend/`
- tRPC routes: `backend/trpc/routes/`
- Type definitions: `backend/types/db.ts`
- ALWAYS redeploy after any backend file change:
```powershell
cd backend
railway up --service grit-backend
cd ..
```
Never assume backend changes are live without redeploying. Never skip this step.

### Database & Auth
- Supabase (project ref: iazdfbqwudlodozgoyov)
- Auth: Supabase Auth (auth.users table)
- Every new auth user automatically gets a profile via database trigger — never manually insert profiles on signup
- All schema changes via Supabase SQL Editor — never via code
- After every schema change: `NOTIFY pgrst, 'reload schema';`
- After schema changes, always update `backend/types/db.ts` immediately

### Data Fetching
- tRPC via `trpcQuery()` and `trpcMutate()` from `@/lib/trpc` for most operations
- Direct Supabase client for auth, profiles, and real-time queries
- React Query keys MUST include userId: `['resource', 'action', user?.id ?? '']`
- Queries requiring auth: `enabled: !!user?.id && !isGuest`
- staleTime: 5 * 60 * 1000 for non-real-time data

