## SECTION 3 — DATABASE SCHEMA

### Tables (public schema)
```
profiles              — user profiles (id = auth.users.id)
challenges            — all challenges
challenge_tasks       — tasks belonging to a challenge
active_challenges     — user's joined challenges
check_ins             — daily task completions
activity_events       — feed events (joins, completions, streaks)
challenge_participants — members of a challenge
streaks               — streak tracking
user_achievements     — badges and milestones
stories               — proof photos / posts
story_views           — who viewed a story
invite_tracking       — referral and invite links
```

### Critical FK Rules
- active_challenges.user_id → profiles.id (NOT auth.users.id directly)
- Never insert into active_challenges without confirming the user has a profile
- New auth users get profiles automatically via trigger — do not duplicate this in code

### Visibility Values — ALWAYS UPPERCASE
- 'PUBLIC', 'FRIENDS', 'PRIVATE' — never lowercase
- Backend enforces .toUpperCase() on insert
- All queries must filter with uppercase values

### Challenge Status Values
- 'published' — live and joinable
- 'draft' — not visible
- 'archived' — no longer active

### challenges Table Key Columns
id, title, description, duration_days, difficulty, category, status, visibility,
participation_type, challenge_type, creator_id, duration_type, live_date,
replay_policy, require_same_rules, show_replay_label, run_status, team_size,
shared_goal_target, shared_goal_unit, deadline_type, deadline_date,
starts_at, ends_at, updated_at, rules, reset_type, max_participants

### active_challenges Table Key Columns
id, user_id, challenge_id, status, started_at, start_at, end_at, created_at

