## SECTION 5 — BUSINESS RULES

### Challenge Limits
- Free users: maximum 2 active challenges at once
- Paid users (GRIIT Pro): unlimited active challenges
- Enforce this check BEFORE inserting into active_challenges
- When free user tries to join a 3rd challenge: show paywall screen

### Streak System
- A day is "secured" when ALL required tasks for that day are completed
- Free users: 2 streak freezes total (lifetime, not per-week)
- Paid users: 5 streak freezes total
- Freeze consumed automatically on missed day if available
- If no freezes remain and user misses a day: streak resets to 0
- Streak reset must trigger a push notification within 1 hour

### Paywall Trigger — CRITICAL
- NEVER show paywall before user completes their first task
- Show paywall at the exact moment user tries to join their 2nd challenge
- Plans: Monthly, Annual
- Payment system: RevenueCat (scaffolded — activate in v2)
- Do NOT remove RevenueCat scaffolding

### Task Verification Types
- JOURNAL  — user writes text (minimum 50 characters)
- TIMER    — user stays on screen with countdown, cannot background app
- PHOTO    — user uploads a photo as proof
- MANUAL   — honor system, user taps complete
- CHECKIN  — location-based (v2 — do not build yet)
- HEALTH   — Apple Health / Whoop (v2 — do not build yet)

### The "Aha Moment" Rule
- The aha moment for GRIIT = user completes first task + sees "Day 1 Secured"
- This MUST happen within the first session
- Every flow decision should be optimized to get users to this moment faster
- Remove any step between signup and first task completion that isn't absolutely necessary

