## SECTION 6 — DESIGN SYSTEM

### Source of Truth
- ALL colors, typography, spacing, radius, shadows: lib/design-system.ts
- ALL component tokens: theme/griit-design-tokens.ts
- NO raw hex values anywhere except lib/design-system.ts
- NO Object.assign in lib/design-system.ts — all exports flat and static
- NO inline styles with hardcoded values — always use design tokens

### Core Colors
```
Page background:     DS_COLORS.BG_PAGE        = #F5F5F5  (cool neutral grey)
Card surface:        DS_COLORS.BG_CARD        = #FFFFFF  (pure white)
Primary accent:      DS_COLORS.ACCENT_PRIMARY = #E8593C  (GRIIT fire orange)
Accent dark:         DS_COLORS.ACCENT_DARK    = #D4472B  (pressed state)
Accent tint:         DS_COLORS.ACCENT_TINT    = #FFF0ED  (light orange bg)
Text primary:        DS_COLORS.TEXT_PRIMARY   = #111111
Text secondary:      DS_COLORS.TEXT_SECONDARY = #666666
Text muted:          DS_COLORS.TEXT_MUTED     = #999999
Success green:       DS_COLORS.ACCENT_GREEN   = #2D7A4F
Success tint:        DS_COLORS.GREEN_BG       = #EBF5EE
Border:              DS_COLORS.BORDER         = #E8E5DF
Divider:             DS_COLORS.DIVIDER        = #EEEBE5
Shadow:              DS_COLORS.SHADOW         = rgba(0,0,0,0.06)
```

### Challenge Header Colors (deep saturated — by category)
```
FITNESS:    #2D1810  (deep rust/ember — intensity and physical heat)
MIND:       #1A1A2E  (deep navy/indigo — focus and cognitive depth)
DISCIPLINE: #1A3A2A  (deep forest green — power and military precision)
FAITH:      #1A1A2E  (same as MIND)
Default:    #2D1810  (fitness/ember as safe default)
```
Why deep saturated darks instead of black or warm brown:
- Pure black headers feel premium/heavy (Spotify) — wrong energy for action-oriented app
- Warm brown headers feel casual (coffee shop) — wrong for discipline app
- Deep domain colors create subconscious category meaning before user reads a word

### Eyebrow Label Rules (replaces "STANDARD")
- NEVER use "STANDARD" as an eyebrow label — it is a dead label
- Use live meaningful data instead:
  - "🔥 {count} ACTIVE TODAY" when count > 0
  - "⚡ 24-HOUR CHALLENGE" for daily challenges
  - "🏆 FEATURED" for featured challenges
  - "✓ CREATOR VERIFIED" for verified challenges
  - "🆕 NEW" for challenges created in last 7 days

### Difficulty Badge Colors (filled pills — not text only)
```
Easy:    green filled  — bg: DS_COLORS.GREEN_BG,   text: DS_COLORS.ACCENT_GREEN
Medium:  amber filled  — bg: #FFF8E8,               text: #C17D00
Hard:    orange filled — bg: DS_COLORS.ACCENT_TINT, text: DS_COLORS.ACCENT_PRIMARY
Extreme: red filled    — bg: #FFE5E5,               text: #DC2626
```

