ONE primary CTA per screen. All secondary actions must be visually subordinate.

### Tab Bar Rules
```
Active icon:          DS_COLORS.ACCENT_PRIMARY (#E8593C)
Inactive icon:        #AAAAAA
Center create button: #111111 circle, white + icon, 54px diameter
Tab bar background:   #FFFFFF with top border 0.5px DS_COLORS.BORDER
```

### Empty State Rules
- NEVER show a blank screen or just "Be the first" text
- Every empty state must be an invitation to action:
  - No active challenges → show "Start Building" + Explore Challenges CTA
  - No activity feed → show "Join a challenge to see your community move"
  - No friends → show "Invite friends" prompt
  - 0 members in challenge → show "Be the first to start something real"
- Empty states are retention opportunities, not dead ends

### Day Secured Celebration Rules
- When ALL tasks complete: screen must transform
- CTA button turns DS_COLORS.ACCENT_GREEN with "Day Secured ✓"
- Brief confetti/pulse animation plays (use react-native-reanimated)
- Copy changes to: "You showed up. Day X secured."
- Shows: tomorrow's task preview + current streak count
- Haptic feedback: trigger heavy impact haptic (Haptics.impactAsync)
- This is the highest-value emotional moment in the entire app

### Animation & Haptic Rules
- Task completion: checkmark animation + medium haptic
- Day secured: confetti + heavy haptic
- Streak milestone (7, 14, 30, 75 days): full celebration screen
- Never use animations that delay user action — keep under 300ms
- Use react-native-reanimated for all animations

### No Gradients Rule
- NEVER use gradients anywhere in the app
- All surfaces must be flat solid colors
- Gradients age fast and look cheap on mobile without a full design team

