## SECTION 7 — COPY & TONE RULES

GRIIT's copy must reinforce user identity, not just confirm actions.

### Replace Generic Copy With Identity Copy
```
❌ "Task completed"          → ✅ "Secured."
❌ "Done"                    → ✅ "You showed up."
❌ "Challenge joined"        → ✅ "Day 1 starts now."
❌ "Error occurred"          → ✅ Specific error message, always
❌ "Loading..."              → ✅ Context-specific: "Loading your challenges..."
❌ "No data available"       → ✅ Invitation to action (see Empty State Rules)
❌ "Continue"                → ✅ "Secure Today" or "Start [Task Name]"
❌ "Submit"                  → ✅ "Commit" or "Lock It In"
❌ "Standard"  (label)       → ✅ Live social proof (see Eyebrow Label Rules)
```

### Push Notification Copy (Days 1–7 retention window)
```
Day 1 (same time as signup): "Day 1 is waiting. Don't let it slip."
Day 2 (if no task done):     "Your streak starts today. Not tomorrow."
Day 3:                       "3 days in. Most people quit here. You're not most people."
Day 7:                       "7 days. You're 3.6x more likely to finish now. Keep going."
```

